values: School has started and it is alright for the most part... I never update this so I'm just gunna write anything. My weekend was long and fun and tiring and I am still tired from it. Ok Im done writing Buh Bye

OK so I've been really busy lately so some stuff happened that I dont really feel like writing about but some other stuff happened that was a lot of fun and its been so long since I wrote anything in this thing that I'm not going to go over it all. I cant believe that school is almost here that really sucks. I have had to much fun this summer and havent really been home so school is gunna be like staring a wall til June... yuck! Ok I'm bored and I need to find something to do... Cya

So I haven't written in this for a while so I don't really know where to start... Hmmm I dropped out of my AP class so maybe I will be in classes with more of the people I never see this year... Yay we aren't little freshmen anymore!!! Well freshmen year was fun anyway.

Friday I went to Lake George for my friend Kristen's parents wedding. The wedding was on Sunday so Friday and Saturday we went on their boat and went tubing aroung the lake. It was a lot of fun. Pretty much all the time that we werent on the lake we were in the hot tub at the house they are staying at or playin pool which we both suck at. Friday nite Kristen played at this weird country bar which was scary and I dont really want to remember anything else about it. Sunday was the wedding and it was at the Sagamore which is really beautiful. Jennifer looked great and the reception was so much fun. Lots of dancing. Monday I came back home and went to the bowling alley with my sister to visit TJ and her boyfriend Mitch.

Tuesday I dont remember doing anything until I bowled at night... yupp Im pretty sure I didnt do anything. Wednesday I went to TJ's house and we went in the pool and played basketball which I was crushed at. Then we went downstairs and played pool (lots of pools) which I think I won 9-ball but that wasn't because I was good at it. After that we watched TV and went to the bowling alley (where else?)... I stayed with him til 8ish n went home n did nothing.

As of today Sara & Mitch have been going out for one month... congrats... awwww... tear.... j/k.

As of tomorrow me & TJ have been going out for six months... congrats 2 us lol almost...

Ok thats it... x1o4x3o... TTYL

Ok so this weekend was bad... Friday I went to Warren, Ohio for the Keystone Tournament of Champions. My parents changed the hotel from one that had an indoor pool (which they didn't know) to this other place that had nothing. Our hotel was in a city like thing where no one was on the streets AT ALL!!! What kind of city is like that??? The only thing that was at our hotel were pool tables so thats pretty much what I did the entire time I was at the hotel. Then that nice I was talking to TJ who I missed oh so much already and he told me more not so good news so umm yea I wasn't in the best mood. I bowled on Saturday and was really bad so since only the top 8 make it to the finals, I obviously didn't. I saw Paula for the first time since New Years so that was kinda nice. Next year I'm gunna qualify to go back and bowl sooooo much better... I hope... Warren was boring. Maybe Cleveland rocks, well Warren definately doesn't. Now I am home bored out of my mind, I just finished the People Magazine cross-word puzzle... so I'm done typing... TTYL

The Biology regents on Friday was the boringest thing ever!!! I finished soooo early and they wont let u leave early which is bull shit... the whole test is a joke. stupid state. Then I came home, got my stuff and went to TJ's house so we could go to Lake George for the weekend. Everyone's campers were so nice, i want one! So we went in the pool and then sat around the campfire til 1 in the morning was really funny... 

Then Saturday we went to Great Escape which is small and sucked... It was me, TJ, Nick, Mitch, Bobby, Anthony, Sarah, and Matt... I guess it was still fun but all the rides there are too small and too slow. We played volleyball in the sand with a monster ball which was kinda cool. Then we went back with 8 people in the car that holds 5 and ordered pizza. We sat around the campfire til 1 again playing the name game, we didn't finish we were just too tired to keep playing... 

Yesterday before we left we played volleyball again at the camp ground and Stefani rode Brandon's bike into the volleyball net and fell... It was pretty funny to watch and she wasnt hurt so it was ok... Then we came back and stopped at some rest stop where we got milkshakes... it was the worst milkshake ever, it was just milk, really gross. Then I went back to TJ's house for a little while and then to (where else?) the bowling alley. I didnt stay there too long but TJ had to work... probably fell asleep because I knew I was going to... That was pretty much my weekend... and I'm sick of typing now so I'm gunna go... TTYL

Only one more test to go, than school is really over!!!! Okay so yesterday TJ and I went to the movies and we saw the Stepford Wives, now for once we both agree on how it was.... it SUCKED!!!! Totally could not have been any worse and the most horrible movie that either of us has ever seen. So, if you are going to the movies and don't care what you are going to see like we didn't, don't see that anyway!!!!
After the movies my mom brought us back to my house where my parents decided to be weirder than usual and probably scared TJ and were even beginning to scare me... uh yeah. So then we went bowling and he was really good, and I was ummm ok I guess but not really good. Sam is also still mad at me so I'm still sorry even though I didn't really say anything but ok.
Mitchell was finally going to talk to my sister!!! awwww... but my sister was not cooperating at all. I'm gunna hafta talk to her about that. It'll happen eventually... Adam you can't go out with my sister!!!! lol pedafile (I don't think that's how it's spelled)
Okay that's it... 143 TTYL

My AP class is over for the year!!!! Except for all the frickin outlines I hafta do, but I'll get over that... 2 more tests til I'm out for the summer. This summer is gunna be the best eva... so excited... I have a new webpage www.geocities.com/steph_bowl23 its not really working that well tho. This weekend was cool. Next weekend I am probably going camping at Lake George with everybody n we r goin to Six Flags so I hafta go on every ride!!!! Fun fun fun... Well I think I reformatted this so I'm gunna c how it looks... TTYL

Rite now I'm in English & Caitlin is complaining about not being able to get on the computer. Today has been soooo much fun!!! Except there hasnt been any senior pranks and that really sucks!!! its supposed to be a tradition, when we are seniors there should be a really good prank... Yay parties parties parties... this year has been full of memories so I'm almost sad that its over but, its over so hell yeah now its gunna be summer!!!! TJ had early dismissal which is NOT fair... I have 3 tests next week... fun fun... visit my website, www.geocities.com/steph_bowl23... ill put more pictures on there soon, i need to upload them!!! Only 3 more periods to go, and that means 3 more parties!!! Maybe I'll start writing in this again soon. or maybe not, idk... Bells gunna ring soon. ttyl

This is the boringest (not really a word) week ever and it doesnt look like its gunna get ne better... JOY... Sunday was fun n maybe ill feel like writing about it sumtime, but not now cuz idk what i feel like doing now besides the nothingness that im doing now...

Ok, so this weekend was pretty good... I have a ton of outlines to do now for my AP class becuz I neglected to do ne of them over the weekend. Friday nite was umm... interesting. All the Friday nite leagues are over so we all decided to go to the movies. Well besides TJ, who also likes to try to annoy me... its kinda like having a bunch of brothers... Well once again I was almost the only girl. JOY... Then Jess came with Bobby so that was the only thing that stopped me from being alone again. Anyway, they all said they didnt wanna c another girl movie so I said we could c Van Helsing. B4 we got there Joey told Mitch that it wasnt good, which Mitch (that rhymes) told every1 else who instantly didnt wanna c it nemore... We couldve seen sumthing else except nuthin was gunna start around the time Bobby n Jess were coming besides Van Helsing so we saw that neway. The ENTIRE MOVIE I had TJ n Mitch sayin, Steph this is ur fault. They didnt watch the movie at all, even enough to form an opinion that it wasnt good. Thats how much they will go by what Joey says, granted I actually tried to pay attention n it really did suck but thats not the point. We didnt get kicked out of newhere or even yelled at which I was surprised about... quite a shock.
Saturday I had my soccer game which was horrible as always. Again we didnt have enough people to play so we had to use people from the other team... not good. We ended up losing 2-0. More later

Today was kinda fun... Lunch was anyway. This nasty (not like mean like gross) kid always sits next to me n we always tell him to go away but he wont listen. So anyway, this girl comes over n man if I thought the other kid was weird ::whoah:: she is worse. Amanda had pretzels again and Caitlin went to shoot one at Amanda but instead it hit the weird girl rite in the forehead! wow that was funny! Then she started writing on the weird kid n then on his notebook, so I go is she ur girlfriend? N he says it would appear that way! That was pretty gross so we told Keli n shes like EWWWWWWW really loud, it was sooooo funny!!! N then Brent started sayin all this stuff like "ask her if she has a dick" and "I wonder who the woman is in the relationship" lol... Then when we were walkin out Brent goes have u ever seen the texas chainsaw massacre? n im like no so hes like well the crazy guy who kills everybody, thats who that girl reminds me of!!!!!! OMG that was the greatest lunch!!!!! LMAO.
Now I have to go write a f***in essay for my AP class becuz that is just so much fun n then do the outlines for that class, & my math n German hw so I can go watch Sam play softball against Ketcham. Ketcham is gunna lose again, thats sad.
Last nite at the awards thing it was really really obvious that John Jay gets everything... for example, Mr. Jutton called Ketcham "the other school" what the fuck was up with that? Their bands: sucked! N referring to Wappingers Jr. High as Wapp. Junior, doesnt that sound wonderful coming from a Van Wyck teacher, yeah they pissed me off. N for the records, Mrs. Simmons is anything but unbiased!!!!!!!! TTYL

Wow I haven't written in this in a while... Lots of stuff has been going on. I've discovered an amazing effect that Dr.Pepper has on me... I get ReaLLy HyPeR!!!!! OMG a couple weeks ago I was runnin around back n forth like CRAZY!!! TJ & Laurel n pretty much everybody was like whoah Steph... n then I crash n can pretty much fall asleep in like one second. 
Last week I also had an English project that kept me from writing in this, n talking to every1 so it pretty much destroyed my social life.
Friday nite I had to go to Sam & TJ's confirmation... what a ton of fun that was... yeah rite! The dude made it take FOREVER!!! but it was ok.
Saturday was boring until I went to the mall with my dad n then I went to the bowlin alley... hot pink cake=good! & then I won a hot pink tweety football that I had wanted for a few weeks now! I was gunna spend all my money until I got it. Then everyone made fun of it. For example my dad "what r u doing with that faggy football?" ok it was funny but I like it! n then we bowled and lost first place which was very depressing... I still think it was my fault cuz I missed a couple easy things that cost us the game. We never win. I cried all the way home. That probably sounds pathetic, but it meant a lot to win with my dad in his last year of this league n now we cant. Yup so that kinda sucked.
Sunday TJ's mom drove us to the movies and we saw 13 Going on 30... it was ok. A lot of food ended up on the floor, but thats what those people get paid for. Then we went back to his house n watched sum more movies n stuff. It was fun. Definately the better part of the weekend.
OK thats the end of my weekend... TTYL

Yay its finally FRIDAY!!!!!! Me n TJ 3 Months: TODAY!!! yay!!!! I think there are 546 days until I can be cool like Don n have my license... probably wont try to pimp it out tho lol... Everything has gone pretty smoothly today, still nervous about my report card coming. I know a 90. sumthing average isnt bad but my grades went down again so my parents are gunna be angry! Yikes! I get to go to the bowling alley early tonite cuz my parents are going to a party... fun... The Yankees lost last nite... that sucks! Jeter is like in a slump or sumthing cuz he isnt hittin the ball for shit! This is another good song... my mom calls it devil music, its not! Maybe its not postive messages but I can deal with it. Luckily Jackie's mom drove me home from school so I didnt have to walk in the rain. I liked school being so empty cuz of the Junior Prom tonite. Definately could get used to it not being overcrowded. OK thats all for now.... TTYL

Okay I have to go do sum homework maybe cuz I have soccer practice at 6!!!! Me n TJ- 3 Months TOMORO!!!! TTYL

Today was actually pretty good... nuthin too bad happened. Actually nuthin at all happened. Ummm i guess it was kinda boring then. Maybe Ill go outside later... TTYL

Today was alright, We played an ok game in gym, it was like a scavenger hunt... lol ummm we went to the wrong place thanks to Jill but we picked it up after that. I wanted to go to John Jay to watch Sam play vs Ketcham but I can't. 

I'd like to wish my dad a Happy Birthday and also Caitlin a Happy 3 quarters Birthday!!!!!! LoL she keeps track of these things. It is also 420 day, idk who cares about that but if ne1 does, Happy 420 Day...

Manny is planning a bowlin meeting for Thursday after school cuz we were supposed to get sweatshirts like 2 or 3 months ago... Its gettin kinda hot for sweatshirts now but I still want it.

There are only 3 days until Me n TJ's 3 Month Anniversary!!!! yay!!!

TTYL

That would have to make this one of the worst days ever... Anyway I'm done complaining for now and maybe I will even start my homework soon, there's a thought. TTYL
